-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group Bank, New World Resources Are Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-06-25T14:41:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/czech-stocks-erste-group-bank-new-world-resources-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
dropped the most since May 9, sliding 2.4 percent to 878.4 at
the end of trading in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   of  Austria  lost 5.4 percent
to 351.6 koruna, its biggest slump in 4 1/2 months. Financial
stocks were among the biggest decliners in Europe on concern a
meeting of leaders this week will fail to contain the region’s
debt crisis.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, dropped 1.2 percent to 99 koruna, its fourth day
of declines and the longest rout in five weeks.  Europe ’s
benchmark coal derivatives retreated 1.2 percent to $97.60 a
metric ton in the Netherlands.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
